<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
  <title>Test Page for SorceryDB ext-decklist</title>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <style type="text/css">
  .col {
    width: 800px;
    float: left;
    margin: 20px;
  }
  fieldset {
      margin: 20px 0px;
  }
  .styled {
    font-family: Tahoma,Verdana,Segoe,sans-serif;
    font-size:15px;
    line-height: 20px;
    color: #333;
    border: 1px solid #aaa;
    background: #f6f6f6;
  }
  .styled .nrdb-ext-decklist-card a {
    text-decoration: none;
    color: chocolate;
  }
  .styled article > * {
      padding: 0 1em;
  }
  .styled header {
      border-bottom: 1px solid silver;
      padding-bottom: 1em;
  }
  .styled header h3 {
      text-decoration: underline;
  }
  .styled header .nrdb-ext-decklist-card {
      margin-bottom: 1em;
      font-variant: small-caps;
      font-size: large;
  }
  .styled header .nrdb-ext-decklist-card  a {
      color: darkred;
  }
  .styled header .nrdb-ext-decklist-stat {
      font-size: small;
  }
  .styled .nrdb-ext-decklist-content h4 {
    margin-bottom: .5em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: brown;
  }
  .styled section .nrdb-ext-decklist-card {
      display: list-item;
      list-style: square;
      margin-left: 2em;
  }
  .styled footer {
      border-top: 1px solid silver;
      margin-top: 2em;
      color: darkgray;
      font-size: small;
  }
  .styled footer a {
      color: dimgray;
  }
  </style>
  </head>
  <body>
      <h1>Decklist Embedding</h1>
      <section>
          <p>Using a special script, you can embed any decklist from SorceryDB into your web pages. Just paste the small piece of code found on the decklist page, into your HTML document.</p>
          <p>The code looks like this:<br>
              <tt style="color:blue">&lt;div </tt><tt style="color:red">data-id</tt><tt style="color:blue">="{{ id }}" </tt><tt style="color:red">data-columns</tt><tt style="color:blue">="3" </tt><tt style="color:red">data-stats</tt><tt style="color:blue">="no" class="nrdb-ext-decklist"></tt><tt style="color:green">&lt;script src="{{ app.request.getSchemeAndHttpHost() ~ '/ext-decklist.js' }}">&lt;/script></tt><tt style="color:blue">&lt;/div></tt>
          </p>
          <p>The 3 attributes in red control the decklist that is displayed:
              <ul>
                  <li><tt style="color:red">data-id</tt> is the id of the decklist</li>
                  <li><tt style="color:red">data-columns</tt> is the number of columns on which the decklist is displayed (default: 1)</li>
                  <li><tt style="color:red">data-stats</tt> controls whether the stats of the decklist are displayed ("yes") or not ("no") (default: yes)</li>
              </ul>
          </p>
          <p>
              Here are two examples of embedded decklists, one with no styling, one with some custom styling for demonstration purposes. Both are generated by the same small line of code shown above.
          </p>
      </section>
     <section class="col">
      <h2>No styling</h2>
      <fieldset>
        <legend>Container attributes</legend>
        <p>Id: <input type="text" value="{{ id }}" onchange="document.getElementById('unstyled').setAttribute('data-id', this.value)"></p>
        <p>Columns: <input type="text" value="3" onchange="document.getElementById('unstyled').setAttribute('data-columns', this.value)"></p>
        <p>Stats: <input type="checkbox" onchange="document.getElementById('unstyled').setAttribute('data-stats', this.checked ? 'yes' : 'no')"></p>
      </fieldset>
      <div class="unstyled">
        <div data-id="{{ id }}" data-columns="3" data-stats="no" class="nrdb-ext-decklist" id="unstyled"><script src="{{ app.request.getSchemeAndHttpHost() ~ '/ext-decklist.js' }}"></script></div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="col">
      <h2>Custom styling</h2>
      <fieldset>
        <legend>Container attributes</legend>
        <p>Id: <input type="text" value="{{ id }}" onchange="document.getElementById('styled').setAttribute('data-id', this.value)"></p>
        <p>Columns: <input type="text" value="2" onchange="document.getElementById('styled').setAttribute('data-columns', this.value)"></p>
        <p>Stats: <input type="checkbox" checked onchange="document.getElementById('styled').setAttribute('data-stats', this.checked ? 'yes' : 'no')"></p>
      </fieldset>
      <div class="styled">
        <div data-id="{{ id }}" data-columns="2" class="nrdb-ext-decklist" id="styled"><script src="{{ app.request.getSchemeAndHttpHost() ~ '/ext-decklist.js' }}"></script></div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </body>
</html>
